data.title: Woman gets trapped in odd position between rails before police rescue her
data.text:
Source:Global Times Published: 2013-10-23 22:03:01

Police rescued a young woman who got stuck in an odd position, between the narrow rails of a barricade outside a bus station by Kemao Market in Beijing's Haidian district on Wednesday.

The woman had lost consciousness and was foaming at the mouth when she fell and became strangely entangled in the rails.

She was rushed to a nearby hospital for treatment, but remained in critical condition as of press time.

Video surveillance showed the woman walking along normally before suddenly slumping, trying to grab on to the rails to steady herself, before ultimately getting stuck in the barricade, said police. The woman, 26, was on her way to work when she fell, another woman, who identified herself as the woman's sister, told media.
